Content C: Are rangefinders a great thing for golf? Yes, they areIs this the rangefinder you want? NOI had an old bushnell that I loved- right up until someone stole it from my cartI could not find a used one like it, so I opted to purchase a medalist, from someone on e-bayI thought I'd spend the extra money to get the "pin-seeker" technologyFirst, this model does not work a bit better than my old oneIn fact, I generally find that it has a harder time finding the pin, not an easier oneAnd then there's the cover for the battery....It arrived with the cover off, which should have been my first clueIt would not snap on, and it took about a gram's worth of pressure for it to fall off- without un-latching itI took it to a local golf store, and they were willing to exchange itI used the new one today, and the cover fell off 4x during the round, just sitting in the golf cartYou can tape it on, but I don't think you should have to duct-tape something that is $250It's a very poor design, to have the cover piece fit over a curveThe case for it looks like it cost bushnell about 10 cents to make, and was sewn by a blind man....- pretty disconcerting for such an expensive gadgetI love having a rangefinder, but I am extremely disappointed that bushnell has such poor quality controlI only wish I had purchased it on , because then i could send it back!

Content B: Product Description : Baby Outlet Covers Insulate Against Drafts Choose these safety outlet covers if you want to childproof your electrical outlets with a quality sliding door outlet cover made in the USA for both child safety and insulation. This Brown Decora care cover replaces a two screw Decora style outlet cover. This safety outlet cover helps protect your children from electrical shocks or burn injuries to fingers or hands from electrical outlets. CareCovers replace standard electrical outlet covers to improve baby safety. An energy saving insulating gasket around the perimeter of the outlet cover seals against air leakages into and out of your home. We sell bulk to save you money and to protect the environment from unnecessary packaging. Major Features of the CareCover Child Safety Outlet Cover: Child Restraint Design: Spring-loaded sliding doors automatically keep receptacle holes covered when not in use. This gives the cover a solid appearance, concealing the black receptacle holes which are so inviting to toddlers. Because of its child safety effectiveness, the CareCover was selected for use by the National Institute of Children's Environments in "California Showcase 1989." Remodeling Function and Economy: Remodeling? CareCovers cover electrical outlets so a color change is simple. Cover with white, off white, ivory or brown sliding panel outlet covers. This child safety outlet care cover conceals wall outlets. Energy Efficiency: An insulating gasket around the entire cover seals against air leakages into and out of your home. The Minneapolis Blower door test is used in the industry to measure energy loss. The blower test was conducted on a house with standard electrical outlet covers. Content A: John M. Browning, American Gunmaker is the authentic biography of the man many have called "The World's Greatest Gun Inventor" A 100-page photographically illustrated technical section describes all John M. Browning inventionsShow More Show Less
Content B: Editorial ReviewsAmazon.com ReviewKnown in many circles as "the world's greatest gun inventor," John M. Browning made his first firearm at the age of 13 but didn't stop there, eventually receiving 128 gun patents in his lifetime. Now you can learn how he did it in John M. Browning: American Gunmaker, the authentic biography of the man who invented pistols, rifles, and shotguns for Winchester, Remington, Colt, Fabrique Nationale, and others. Browning's most successful firearms included the M1911 pistol, the Browning .50-caliber machine gun, the Browning automatic rifle, and the groundbreaking Browning Auto-5 semiautomatic machine gun. His Colt 1911, Browning 1917/19, and BAR were popular among the U.S. forces during World War I, World War II, and the Korean War, while some of his other military weapons--such as the Browning Hi-Power, M2 Browning machine gun--are still in use today around the world. John M. Browning: American Gunmaker includes a 100-page photographically illustrated technical section that describes all of Browning's inventions.

Content B: Product Description : Color: PurpleCarpooling? Vacationing? Squeezing three kids across the backseat? This revolutionary inflatable car seat is ideal to keep on hand! It meets all U.S. and European safety standards, yet deflates to fit in a handbag. This compact, portable booster inflates in one quick minute and weighs less than 1 lb. Winner of the JPMA Innovation Award Meets tough European safety standards, even when deflated! European regulations require that child safety seats be tested in the "worst case scenario." To pass testing, the car seat was inflated, deflated, and then crash tested. The portable car seat is designed to position the vehicle's seatbelt correctly and will prevent "submarining" (i.e., slipping under the seat belt) in a crash. Content A: Children never have to be without a booster seat again - light, compact design No need to carry a bulky booster seat Easily carried in backpacks For children aged 4 - 11, 33 - 80 pounds Folds into the convenient carrying bag included with the seat and also includes a shoulder belt postioner
Content B: Product Description : Color: PurpleCarpooling? Vacationing? Squeezing three kids across the backseat? This revolutionary inflatable car seat is ideal to keep on hand! It meets all U.S. and European safety standards, yet deflates to fit in a handbag. This compact, portable booster inflates in one quick minute and weighs less than 1 lb. Ideal for caregivers, taxi rides, rental cars, and more. For kids 4 years and up, from 40-80 lbs. and 3'4"-4'9" tall. Storage pouch and shoulder belt positioning strap included. Imported. Winner of the JPMA Innovation Award Meets tough European safety standards, even when deflated! European regulations require that child safety seats be tested in the "worst case scenario." To pass testing, the car seat was inflated, deflated, and then crash tested. The portable car seat is designed to position the vehicle's seatbelt correctly and will prevent "submarining" (i.e., slipping under the seat belt) in a crash. Invented by a Nationally Certified Child Passenger Safety Technician (CPST), who is also the mother of two Car booster seat measures 13"L x 13"W x 4 1/2"H inflated; deflates to fit in a 12"L x 6"W pouch Only for use with a three-point seat belt
Content C: Hello.I am a EMT student.This is very well builtThe light is very bright, maybe a little too bright when I'm shining it in people eyesIt comes with a little slip-on guard to narrow the light, it is nice to have, but slipps off sometimesThe light is very thin, and the clip moves up and down, making it fit good in your shirt pocketI will say that the AAAA batteries are allitle abnormal, But Radio Shack and Wal-Greens have them.This light is worth the 15 or so dollars._TRV

Content C: Hey, this little bb gun looks swell with it's sleek black barrel and wooden butt and pump/gripI bought it to shoot at cans in my back yardAnd, it is adequate, but not a terrific amount of funIt got a wonderful writeup by a seller on gunbroker.comHowever..It is not easy to load bbs into the small hole and, often, many are spilledYou will have to adjust to the pumpThe first few times, I squeezed my fingersThe chambering device is not terrificIt is almost necessary to hold the toy upside down to insure that a bb goes into the chamberFinally, the wooden butt stock is held into place by one screw, not two or moreThis allows the butt to wiggle from side to side when it is not constantly retightenedIt rather makes me upset that highly paid Crosman execs make tons of money, but never try out their own product

Content C: Hmm...it's already been four months and I used it about three weeks before my real bed arrivedFirst, if you consider this as a substitution of a real bed, consider it againIt could be used temporarily, not recommended for permanent useMy wife told me you might get your back hurt if you keep sleeping over itSecond, I think the air bed itself is pretty goodThe surface material feels goood, and built-in AC pump works fineThe noise while pumping up the bed is kind of disturbing, but it's tolerableHowever, you have to hear that noise repeatedly because the air keeps flowing out little by littleSo you have to feed it once 3~4 daysI have it currently, and I think I can set it up for my friends visiting and staying over my house
